dcterms:creator: Alex Krizhevsky
Ilya Sutskever
Geoffrey Hinton
dcterms:description: CIFAR-10 is a dataset consisting of 60,000 32x32 color images in 10 different classes, with 6,000 images per class. It is commonly used for training machine learning models in image classification tasks.
dcterms:title: CIFAR-10

dcterms:creator: Alex Krizhevsky
Ilya Sutskever
Geoffrey Hinton
dcterms:description: CIFAR-100 is similar to CIFAR-10 but contains 100 classes with 600 images each. The classes are grouped into 20 superclasses, making it a more challenging dataset for image classification.
dcterms:title: CIFAR-100

dcterms:creator: Yuval Netzer
Tao Wang
Adam Coates
Alessandro Bissacco
Bo Wu
Andrew Y. Ng
dcterms:description: SVHN (Street View House Numbers) is a dataset of over 600,000 labeled digits obtained from images of house numbers in Google Street View. It is used for digit recognition tasks.
dcterms:title: SVHN

dcterms:creator: Kaiming He
Xiangyu Zhang
Shaoqing Ren
Jian Sun
dcterms:description: ImageNet is a large visual database designed for use in visual object recognition software research. It contains over 1.2 million images across 1,000 classes.
dcterms:title: ImageNet

dcterms:description: Occ. CIFAR-10 is a variant of the CIFAR-10 dataset where images are occluded by a black box, used to evaluate the robustness of models under occlusion.
dcterms:title: Occ. CIFAR-10

dcterms:description: Stanford Cars is a dataset containing images of cars, annotated with class labels for different car models. It is used for fine-grained image classification tasks.
dcterms:title: Stanford Cars
